# EZM0.2 Project Cursor Rules

# Project Structure
- Follow Next.js 13+ App Router conventions
- Keep components in appropriate feature directories
- Maintain consistent file naming across the application

# Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., MoveCard.tsx, AddressForm.tsx)
- Pages: page.tsx (Next.js convention)
- API Routes: route.ts (Next.js convention)
- Utilities: camelCase (e.g., formatDate.ts, validateAddress.ts)
- Types/Interfaces: PascalCase with Type/Interface suffix (e.g., MoveType.ts, UserInterface.ts)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (e.g., API_ENDPOINTS.ts, STATUS_CODES.ts)

# Component Guidelines
- Use functional components with TypeScript
- Implement proper prop typing
- Follow atomic design principles (atoms, molecules, organisms)
- Reuse existing components from the project before creating new ones
- Keep components focused and single-responsibility

# API Implementation
- Follow RESTful conventions
- Implement proper error handling
- Use Prisma for database operations
- Validate input data
- Return consistent response formats
- Use proper HTTP status codes

# Database Operations
- Use Prisma Client for all database operations
- Implement proper error handling for database operations
- Follow the existing Prisma schema structure
- Use transactions when necessary
- Implement proper indexing as defined in schema

# State Management
- Use React Query for server state
- Use React Context for global UI state
- Use local state for component-specific state
- Implement proper loading and error states

# Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Follow existing design system
- Maintain consistent spacing and typography
- Use responsive design principles
- Keep styles modular and reusable

# Code Quality
- Write clean, self-documenting code
- Add comments for complex logic
- Use TypeScript strictly
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Follow ESLint and Prettier configurations

# Testing
- Write unit tests for critical components
- Implement API route tests
- Test error scenarios
- Maintain good test coverage

# Security
- Implement proper authentication
- Validate all user inputs
- Sanitize data before database operations
- Use environment variables for sensitive data
- Follow OWASP security guidelines

# Performance
- Implement proper loading states
- Use proper image optimization
- Implement proper caching strategies
- Optimize database queries
- Use proper code splitting

# Git Workflow
- Write meaningful commit messages
- Keep commits atomic and focused
- Follow conventional commits format
- Review code before committing
- Keep branches up to date

# Documentation
- Document complex logic
- Keep README up to date
- Document API endpoints
- Document component props
- Document database schema changes

# Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML
- Implement proper ARIA labels
- Ensure proper color contrast
- Support keyboard navigation
- Test with screen readers

# Error Handling
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Show user-friendly error messages
- Log errors appropriately
- Handle edge cases
- Implement proper fallbacks

# Performance Monitoring
- Monitor API response times
- Track component render times
- Monitor database query performance
- Track user interactions
- Monitor error rates

# Code Review Guidelines
- Review for security issues
- Check for performance implications
- Verify accessibility compliance
- Ensure proper error handling
- Validate against existing patterns 